  "doc_id": "51831",
  "text": "where P qq 5 is a probability to find the |uudqq -Fock state in the proton. Considering Eq. (4), one can integrate over x 1 , x 2 , x 3 and x 4 to obtain theq-distribution in the proton. As was mentioned in Ref. [CITATION_1] , the probability of the five-quark Fock state is proportional to 1/m 2 q , where m q is the mass of q(q) in the Fock state |uudqq . Although, the BHPS model prediction for the P qq 5 is suitable when the quarks are heavy, we expect that the light five-quark states have a larger probability in comparison to the heavy five-quark states.",
